snippet.textDisplay: Such an emotional week for VS fans. Few days ago Shahi Hassan sang for the first time in public and mesmerized us with the cover of Namumkin on Pepsi Battle of the Bands, and now this. Members of Vital Signs and Shoaib Mansoor played a huge role in shaping up Pakistan Music Industry. Coke Studio was a project of Rohail Hayat, founder and manager of Vital Signs. He also started Pepsi Battle Of the Bands with Shahi Hassan and Fifi Rehman. I literally couldn't stop my tears. It would have been really amazing if they featured Rohail, Shehzad, Nusrat and Rizwan in this song as well. RIP Junaid and long live Vital Signs.
snippet.textOriginal: Such an emotional week for VS fans. Few days ago Shahi Hassan sang for the first time in public and mesmerized us with the cover of Namumkin on Pepsi Battle of the Bands, and now this. Members of Vital Signs and Shoaib Mansoor played a huge role in shaping up Pakistan Music Industry. Coke Studio was a project of Rohail Hayat, founder and manager of Vital Signs. He also started Pepsi Battle Of the Bands with Shahi Hassan and Fifi Rehman. I literally couldn't stop my tears. It would have been really amazing if they featured Rohail, Shehzad, Nusrat and Rizwan in this song as well. RIP Junaid and long live Vital Signs.
